There is no Go syntax like this. Use an if statement.

The operands of `|` must be integers. The operands of `||` must be booleans.

What&#39;s more, a `string` cannot be `false` or `nil`.

Given that [OP&#39;s actual goal](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58476932/how-to-make-variable-assignment-with-or-in-golang/58476985#comment103286843_58477058) is to supply a default for an environment variable, the test should be on the boolean return value from [os.LookupEnv](https://godoc.org/os#LookupEnv), not the string value.  Use a function like this:

    func getenv(key string, def string) string {
         val, ok := os.LookupEnv(key)
         if !ok {
             val = def
         }
         return val
    }

