You can use [scripted_metric](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/client/net-api/current/scripted-metric-aggregation-usage.html) aggrgegation for this

Query:
````
GET index31/_search
{
  &quot;size&quot;: 0, 
  &quot;aggs&quot;: {
    &quot;doc_length&quot;: {
      &quot;scripted_metric&quot;: {
        &quot;init_script&quot;: {
          &quot;source&quot;: &quot;state.commits = []&quot;
        },
        &quot;map_script&quot;: {
          &quot;source&quot;: &quot;state.commits.add(doc[&#39;books&#39;].length)&quot;
        },
        &quot;combine_script&quot;: {
          &quot;source&quot;: &quot;def sum = 0.0; for (c in state.commits) { sum += c } return sum&quot;
        },
        &quot;reduce_script&quot;: {
          &quot;source&quot;: &quot;def sum = 0.0; for (a in states) { sum += a } return sum&quot;
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
````

